            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "You’re asking:\n\n“How many medals did the USA win in the 2024 Summer Olympics?”\n\nHere is the confirmed, verified outcome:\n\n- The United States placed **1st** in the final overall medal standings at the Paris 2024 Summer Olympics, securing a total of **126 medals**. These consisted of:\n  - **40 gold**\n  - **44 silver**\n  - **42 bronze** ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_at_the_2024_Summer_Olympics)).\n\nThis information is corroborated by multiple reputable sources including Wikipedia, the official United States Olympic & Paralympic Committee (USOPC), and NBC Olympics ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_at_the_2024_Summer_Olympics)).\n\nHere are key additional details:\n\n- The United States tied China with **40 gold medals**, but ranked ahead thanks to having more silver medals (44 vs. 27) ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_at_the_2024_Summer_Olympics)).\n- This marked the **fourth consecutive** Summer Olympics—and the **19th overall** in history—that the USA topped the medal table ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_at_the_2024_Summer_Olympics)).\n- According to the USOPC, Team USA also broke down as follows: **40 gold, 44 silver, 42 bronze**, totaling **126 Olympic medals** ([teamusa.com](https://www.teamusa.com/paris-2024/olympics/medals)).\n\nTo recap clearly:\n\n    USA medal haul at the 2024 Summer Olympics (Paris):\n    - Gold: 40\n    - Silver: 44\n    - Bronze: 42\n    - Total: 126\n\nLet me know if you'd like a breakdown by sport or athlete, or how this compares to previous U.S. Olympic performances!",
